post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_5309414_5309431_0": {"length": 27, "quality": 0.9310344827586207, "section_id": 7003}}, "n3337": {"so_5309414_5309431_0": {"length": 27, "quality": 0.9310344827586207, "section_id": 6749}}, "n4659": {"so_5309414_5309431_0": {"length": 27, "quality": 0.9310344827586207, "section_id": 8500}}}, "5309431": {"Id": "5309431", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>It is not necessary, but it helps readability if you only see the derived class definition. </p>\n<p>\u00a710.3 [class.virtual]/3</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_5309414_5309431_0\">If a virtual member function vf is declared in a class Base and in a class Derived, derived directly or indirectly from Base, a member function vf with the same name and same parameter list as Base::vf is declared, then Derived::vf is also virtual (whether or not it is so declared) and it overrides <sup>97)</sup> Base::vf.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Where footnote <sup>97)</sup> basically states that if the argument list differs, the function will not <em>override</em> nor be necessarily <code>virtual</code></p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2011-03-15T08:57:06.417", "Score": "27", "CreationDate": "2011-03-15T08:57:06.417", "ParentId": "5309414", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "36565"}, "5309414": {"ViewCount": "6532", "Body": "<p>Why do I sometimes see in C++ examples when talking about subclassing / inheritance, the base class has virtual keyword and sometimes the overridden function has also the virtual keyword, why it's necessary to add to the subclass the virtual key word sometimes?\nFor example:</p>\n<pre><code>class Base \n{\n  Base(){};\n  virtual void f()\n     ......\n  }\n};\n\nclass Sub : public Base\n{\n  Sub(){};\n  virtual void f()\n     ...new impl of f() ...\n  }\n};\n</code></pre>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "5309431", "Title": "in c++ when subclassing why sometimes need to add virtual keyword to overridden function?", "CreationDate": "2011-03-15T08:55:38.060", "Id": "5309414", "CommentCount": "3", "FavoriteCount": "1", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditDate": "2016-03-22T01:53:42.653", "LastEditorUserId": "839689", "LastActivityDate": "2016-03-22T01:53:42.653", "Score": "19", "OwnerUserId": "63898", "Tags": "<c++><inheritance><virtual-functions>", "AnswerCount": "1"}});